\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b oleifolium }({\i Statice virgata} Willd.): Plant 15-45 cm. Leaves in basal rosettes. Inflorescence-branches 0·5-0·7 mm in diameter when dry, smooth, diverging at not more than 45°; segments 15-35 mm, cylindrical, the lower longer than the upper. Spikelets 1- to 5-flowered. Inner bract 4-4·5 mm, about equalling the calyx. Calyx 4·5-5 mm; limb ½ as long as the tube. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   A highly polymorphic subspecies. Plants with 3- to 5-flowered spikelets (var. {\i majus} (Guss.) Pignatti) are frequent on calcareous cliffs in the southern part of the range and have been described as a distinct species ({\b Statice dubia} Andrews ex Guss.,{\i  Fl. Sic. Prodr., Suppl.} 89 (1832),{\i  S. smithii} Ten.). Intermediates between this subspecies and {\b 30}, {\b 31}, {\b 42}, {\b 47}, {\b 48}, {\b 51} and {\b 85} occur sporadically in areas of contact.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  dictyocladum} Arcangeli,{\i  Comp. Fl. Ital.} ed. 2, 459 (1894): Plant 15-45 cm. Leaves in basal rosettes. Inflorescence branches 0·5-0·7 mm in diameter when dry, diverging at not more than 45°; lower segments longer than the upper. Spikelets 1-flowered. Inner bract c. 5 mm. Calyx 6-7 mm; limb as long as the tube. •{\i  Corse, ?Sardegna}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp.{\b  sardoum }(Pignatti) Pignatti, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  64:} 366 (1971) ({\i L. virgatum} subsp.{\i  sardoum} Pignatti): Plant 5-15(-35) cm. Leaves on somewhat woody basal branches. Inflorescence-branches regularly reticulate, diverging at an angle of (45°-)90°(-120°); segments usually 2-4 mm, subequal, black when dry. Spikelets 2- to 5-flowered. Inner bract up to 4 mm. Calyx c. 4·5 mm; limb as long to 1½ times as long as the tube. •{\i  S. Sardegna} ({\i near Cagliari}).
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp.{\b  pseudodictyocladum} (Pignatti) Pignatti,{\i  loc. cit.} (1971) ({\i L. virgatum} subsp.{\i  pseudodictyocladum} Pignatti): Plant 15-30 cm. Leaves in basal rosettes. Inflorescence-branches 0·5-0·7 mm in diameter when dry, rough, diverging at not more than 45°; segments slightly constricted at the nodes, the lower longer than the upper. Spikelets 2- to 3-flowered. Inner bract 4-4·5 mm. Calyx 4·5-5 mm; limb ½ as long as the tube. {\i Islas Baleares} ({\i S. Mallorca}).
\par

