\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 57. L. carpathum} (Rech. fil.) Rech. fil.,{\i  Denkschr. Akad. Wiss. Math.-Nat. Kl.} ({\i Wien}) {\b 105}({\b 1}): 427 (1943). Plant 20-40 cm, glabrous, rough. Leaves 40-90 × 1-2 mm, linear, fleshy, somewhat subcylindrical, obtuse, 1-veined. Inflorescence without non-flowering branches. Spikes 4-6 cm, with 2-4 spikelets per cm; spikelets (1-)2-flowered. Inner bract c. 5·5 mm; outer bract c. 1·5 mm, overlapping 1/5 of the inner. Calyx c. 5·5 mm. Corolla pale violet. {\i Calcareous cliffs. • Karpathos} ({\i near Vrondi}). Cr.
