\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 58. L. emarginatum} (Willd.) O. Kuntze,{\i  Rev. Gen. Pl.}{\b  2: }395 (1891) ({\i Statice spathulata} var.{\i  emarginata} (Willd.) Boiss.). Plant 30-50 cm, glabrous. Leaves 40-60 × 7-15 mm, linear-spathulate, 1- to 5-veined, truncate to emarginate. Inflorescence cylindrical; non-flowering branches absent; scales 6-7 mm, sometimes the lowest up to 20 mm and leaf-like. Spikes 2-3 cm, lax, with 4 spikelets per cm; spikelets 1(-2)-flowered. Inner bract 5·5-7 mm; outer bract 2-2·5 mm, overlapping 1/5-1/4 of the inner. Calyx 7-8 mm; limb ½ as long as the tube. Corolla 11-12 mm. {\i Rocks near the sea. • Gibraltar.} Hs.
\par

